The MISSISSIPPI. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. February 4, 1903.) No. 70. Appeal from the District Court of the United States for the Southern District of New York. J. Parker Kirlin, for appellant. Lawrence Kneeland, for appellee.

Before WALLACE, LACOMBE, and COXE, Circuit Judges.

No opinion. Decree of District Court affirmed, with interest and costs, on opinion below. 113 Fed. 985.
